						<summary>

						<p>On a pillar in the ruined Narasimhasvāmin temple.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 174 • • • • .</p>						

						<p>Damaged. Seems to register a grant to the temple of Nṛisiṁha at Siṅgarūṭla by a certain Koṇḍaya born in the Pulipāka family and the Ātreya-gōtra.</p>						

